race.comment: PARTY DAY (3) filled a minor placing at Devonport Synthetic two starts back and then didn't have the best of it when well in the market here. Fitter again and has the blinkers on for the first time. This suits and she won't get too many better chances to open her account. SOUTHERN AURORAS (4) wasn't far off maiden success two back here and has been tuned up for her resumption with a trial at Longford. The premier hoop is booked and she jumps from the inside barrier. She will be naturally improved and a bold effort is likely. ZANZI (6) would be a contender at best and resumed here with a solid hitout. Maps well and can get into the finish. WANNABE ZIGGY (5) has some ability and is worth a look freshened.
